Trample		CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:SpecialAttack.Extraordinary.AttackOption	VISIBLE:YES	DEFINE:TrampleDamageDice|0	DEFINE:TrampleDamageDieSize|0	DEFINE:TrampleDamageBonus|0	DEFINE:TrampleDC|0	DESC:As a full-round action, you can attempt to overrun any creature that is at least one size category smaller than you. This works just like the combat maneuver, but you do not need to make a check, and rather merely have to move over opponents in your path. Targets of a trample take %1d%2+%3 points of damage. Targets of the trample can make an attack of opportunity but at a -4 penalty. If targets forego an attack of opportunity, they can attempt to avoid you and receive a Reflex save (DC %4) to take half damage. You can only deal trampling damage to each target once per round, no matter how many times your movement takes you over a target creature.|TrampleDamageDice|TrampleDamageDieSize|TrampleDamageBonus|TrampleDC																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																													BONUS:VAR|TrampleDamageBonus|STR*3/2	BONUS:VAR|TrampleDC|10+(HD/2)+STR	BONUS:VAR|TrampleDC|2|PREFEAT:1,Ability Focus (Trample)				SOURCEPAGE:p.X
